{"key":"processedPost-6997000","value":{"id":6997000,"first":6996955,"last":6997000,"when":1180751372,"utime":"06/02/07 05:29 AM","content":"You can isolate pan mycelium, but it doesn't form rhizomorphs, so you can't isolate for that.  Simply isolate each zone of the mycelium and then fruit out each one to find the best performer.  Most growers take the easy way, and wait until they get a really good flush, and then take a clone.  Store it in a master culture slant as soon as you clean it up on agar.<br />RR","title":"Re: How do you know what substrains of pan mycellium to grab?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}